                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15664.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mine and Smelter Operators Association</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department negotiating to have meeting of mining men in Chihuahua postponed.
                    Meantime, in order that quick action may be <pb facs="1050" n="934"
                        xml:id="pg_934"/> taken in case necessity, your members should keep in close
                    touch with Mr. Carothers and await outcome negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
